Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.69,0:00:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is great and most worthy of . . .”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.24,0:00:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . praise”!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.78,0:00:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.45,0:00:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . worthy of praise in the city of our God,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.03,0:00:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“in his holy mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.79,0:00:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Beautiful in its loftiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.79,0:00:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the joy of the whole earth, is Mount”—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.38,0:00:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.00,0:00:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“Mount Zion”!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.71,0:00:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of you have been paying good attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.55,0:00:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, where is Mount Zion?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.18,0:00:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here, Father. Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.22,0:00:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.27,0:00:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t see it. Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.27,0:00:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Father, we live on Mount Zion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.23,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying we live on a mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.23,0:00:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.53,0:00:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What is so special about Mount Zion?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:00:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.41,0:00:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.70,0:00:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where King David lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.62,0:00:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah said:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.29,0:00:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I have put my king upon Zion,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.66,0:01:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,my holy mountain.’
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.46,0:01:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The priests brought the Ark here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.17,0:01:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hamutal, where did we get such studious children?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.71,0:01:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like their father.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.68,0:01:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, children.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.93,0:01:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.93,0:01:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.50,0:01:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Zephaniah, today my little son
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.00,0:01:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,found this in a field and brought it home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.55,0:01:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re filling the holy city with their filthy idols.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:02:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere I look, I see Baal images
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.81,0:02:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and smoke on the high places.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.69,0:02:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell of their incense makes me sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been king for 12 years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.61,0:02:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s time to act!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.66,0:02:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to finish the cleansing work my grandfather started.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.87,0:02:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You will need Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.04,0:02:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.62,0:02:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been praying about it day and night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.71,0:02:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.84,0:02:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I will issue a proclamation:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the word go forth that we will rid this land of idolatry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve seen these cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.19,0:02:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it or leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep raising your prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.95,0:02:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We start here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.99,0:03:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.09,0:03:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what we will do to every false god in the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.86,0:03:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Father—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.99,0:03:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.95,0:03:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, come on, this is no time to be sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.16,0:03:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah is on a campaign against all the other gods except Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.00,0:03:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.13,0:03:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah is upending his own kingdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.59,0:03:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This will not go down as easily as they think.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.34,0:04:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he think people will give up their customs?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.76,0:04:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,their rituals? their whole way of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.02,0:04:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal will rescue us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.70,0:04:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal will rescue us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.12,0:04:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, look around!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.33,0:04:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All over Judah and Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.41,0:04:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah is destroying Baal images.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.67,0:04:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They can’t even rescue themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.92,0:04:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the people—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.71,0:04:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are supporting him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.13,0:04:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and doubt, you disrespectful child.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You have become disloyal to Baal and to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.89,0:04:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,your father, who gave you life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind, I’ll come up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.24,0:05:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My lady Hamutal, a word with you, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.04,0:05:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A word with you, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ben-Mattan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.51,0:06:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, tell the king he must stop what he’s doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.30,0:06:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.31,0:06:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s endangering himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,his family, and our entire nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.82,0:06:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah’s campaign against Baal worshippers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is a campaign against Baal himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.41,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Ben-Mattan, you and your disgusting idols.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away from me before I have the guards arrest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.29,0:06:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you, just another word, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hamutal, I’m only telling you this for your own safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.14,0:06:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It’d be terrible if something were to happen to the king
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.56,0:06:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,like what happened to his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hamutal,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.28,0:07:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,think of your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.16,0:07:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal worshippers are no match for Jehovah, Hamutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.09,0:07:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don’t be fearful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But this campaign has gone on for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.68,0:07:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How long do we have to endure this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,However long it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Zephaniah the prophet has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.52,0:07:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He brought someone with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.73,0:07:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.53,0:07:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll see them in the throne room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.33,0:07:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Better check on the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.91,0:07:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don’t show your concern in front of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.90,0:08:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, have I gone too far?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My own grandfather didn’t succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in ridding the land of the high places.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.87,0:08:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.76,0:08:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, this is Jeremiah from Anathoth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:08:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The man whom Jehovah has called to be a prophet, welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,King Josiah, all the faithful ones
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,support your campaign against idolatry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.98,0:09:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We have done as you directed, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.19,0:09:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And since you began this campaign 18 months ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.94,0:09:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you have gained many supporters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.41,0:09:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.41,0:09:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, many have continued worshipping Baal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.24,0:09:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Men like Ben-Mattan pose a great threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The people may even resort to violence
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.96,0:09:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to oppose this great work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.21,0:09:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.55,0:09:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.85,0:09:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,do you feel that you may not have
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.47,0:09:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what it takes to complete such a task?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.44,0:09:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Restoring pure worship will take much more effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.65,0:09:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re right, Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:09:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But you’re not doing this in human strength;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:10:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is on your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.75,0:10:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He will give you the courage, wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.83,0:10:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and strength to complete this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.33,0:10:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When I expressed doubt in my own abilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.34,0:10:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah told me: “Do not say, ‘I am just a boy.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.97,0:10:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah spoke to you directly, Jeremiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.18,0:10:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I be sure that he’ll back me up that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.56,0:10:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah just told me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.56,0:10:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of a prophecy given hundreds of years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.81,0:10:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,after King Jeroboam set up his own altar in the northern kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.82,0:10:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“By the word of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.03,0:10:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“a man of God came from Judah to Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.03,0:10:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“while Jeroboam was standing by the altar
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“to make sacrificial smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.04,0:10:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then he called out
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.75,0:10:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“against the altar by the word of Jehovah and said:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.25,0:10:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘O altar, altar!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.92,0:10:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘This is what Jehovah says:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.71,0:10:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“Look! A son named Josiah
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“will be born to the house of David!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.68,0:11:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“He will sacrifice on you the priests of the high places,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.43,0:11:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“those making sacrificial smoke on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.48,0:11:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will burn human bones on you.”’”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.23,0:11:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So do not waver in a lack of faith, Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.82,0:11:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Become powerful by faith,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,like our father Abraham.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.12,0:11:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah also spoke to me, Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.83,0:11:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He said:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.41,0:11:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will wipe out from this place every vestige of Baal,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“the name of the foreign-god priests along with the priests . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.34,0:11:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will call to account the princes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“the sons of the king, and all those wearing foreign clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.35,0:11:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . Neither their silver nor their gold will . . . save them . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.48,0:11:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He will bring to nothing all the gods of the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaphan, the cleansing campaign has gone well,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.89,0:12:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but the temple is in disrepair.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been neglected for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.89,0:12:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I heartily agree, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.31,0:12:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Go up to Hilkiah, the high priest,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.86,0:12:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,let him collect all the silver
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.86,0:12:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that is brought into the house of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.99,0:12:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it to those appointed over the work
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.95,0:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to repair the damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.24,0:12:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them to buy timbers and hewn stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.87,0:12:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good, my lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.04,0:12:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And who should keep account of the funds?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaphan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.21,0:12:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Joah, no accounting should be required for the silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.38,0:12:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All these men are trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.51,0:13:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my lord, as you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.26,0:13:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The day my grandfather died,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.06,0:13:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he spoke of the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.98,0:13:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept this safe all these years,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.81,0:13:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,hoping one day I could glorify Jehovah’s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilkiah! What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.83,0:15:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaphan, I found the book of the Law in the house of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.63,0:15:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The book of the Law?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.89,0:15:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve never seen these passages before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.35,0:15:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this scroll to King Josiah immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.02,0:16:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Materials—as far as that goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we are ahead of schedule for the most part.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.07,0:16:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are a few items that just haven’t come in yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.66,0:16:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we get them in the next week or so—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.58,0:16:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaphan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.91,0:16:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How is the renovation coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.91,0:16:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your servants are doing everything that was assigned to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.71,0:16:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They have poured out the money
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.42,0:16:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that was found in the house of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.25,0:16:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have handed it over
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to the appointed men and to those doing the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.31,0:16:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a book that Hilkiah the priest has given me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.52,0:16:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What book?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.57,0:16:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They appear to be the words of Moses, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.28,0:16:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it to us, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.07,0:16:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“These are the regulations
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the judicial decisions that you should be careful to carry out . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.67,0:17:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“You should completely destroy all the places
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.88,0:17:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“where the nations you will dispossess have served their gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.72,0:17:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“whether on the high mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.72,0:17:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“or on the hills or under any luxuriant tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.76,0:17:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“You should pull down their altars,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.48,0:17:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“shatter their sacred pillars,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“burn their sacred poles in the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.56,0:17:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“and cut down the graven images of their gods,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,obliterating their very names from that place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.51,0:17:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.93,0:17:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you along with Hilkiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.18,0:17:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,inquire of Jehovah concerning the words
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.39,0:17:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the book that has been found,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.89,0:18:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s rage is great
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.31,0:18:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because our forefathers did not carry out the word of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by observing all that is written in this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.96,0:18:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The prophetess Huldah lives nearby in the Second Quarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.00,0:18:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll ask Hilkiah to meet us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.95,0:19:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what Jehovah the God of Israel says:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.00,0:19:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“Tell the man who sent you to me:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.79,0:19:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘. . . I will bring calamity on this place
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.34,0:19:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and its inhabitants,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.71,0:19:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘all the curses that are written in the book
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.17,0:19:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘that they read before the king of Judah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.55,0:19:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Because they have abandoned me
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.26,0:19:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and are making sacrifices smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.56,0:19:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘to other gods in order to offend me . . . ,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘my rage will pour out on this place
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.11,0:19:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will not be extinguished.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.74,0:19:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But to the king of Judah . . . ,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.12,0:19:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what Jehovah the God of Israel says:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.12,0:19:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Because your heart was responsive
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.67,0:19:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“and you humbled yourself before God on hearing his words
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.30,0:19:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . and ripped your garments apart
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.80,0:19:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“and wept before me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.89,0:20:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I also have heard you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.35,0:20:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“I also have heard you . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.35,0:20:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“That is why . . . you will be laid in your grave in peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.02,0:20:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“and your eyes will not see all the calamity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.10,0:20:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that I will bring on this place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.78,0:20:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Praised be Jehovah, our merciful God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.78,0:20:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for holding back his wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.45,0:20:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Summon all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Have them come up to the house of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.09,0:20:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be careful to obey all these words
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.84,0:20:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I am commanding you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.84,0:20:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that it may always go well with you and your sons after you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.05,0:20:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“because you are doing what is good and right
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the eyes of Jehovah your God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.35,0:20:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“When Jehovah your God annihilates
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.44,0:20:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“the nations that you are to dispossess,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.56,0:20:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . do not ask about their gods, saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘How were these nations accustomed to serve their gods?’
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.32,0:21:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . Because they do for their gods
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“every detestable thing that Jehovah hates,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.33,0:21:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“even burning their sons and their daughters
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.00,0:21:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the fire to their gods.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.79,0:21:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“If your brother . . . or your son
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.92,0:21:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“or your daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“or your cherished wife
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.10,0:21:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“or your closest companion
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.89,0:21:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“should try to entice you in secrecy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.10,0:21:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“saying, ‘Let us go and serve other gods,’
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.69,0:21:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . you must not give in to him or listen to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.61,0:21:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“nor should you show pity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.74,0:21:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“or feel compassion or protect him;
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.74,0:21:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.95,0:21:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you should kill him without fail.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.04,0:21:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Observe the month of Abib,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.25,0:22:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“and celebrate the Passover to Jehovah your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.59,0:22:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“for in the month of Abib, Jehovah your God
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“brought you out of Egypt by night.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.26,0:22:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“And you should sacrifice the Passover offering
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.27,0:22:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“to Jehovah your God . . . in the place that Jehovah chooses
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.31,0:22:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to have his name reside.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.65,0:22:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please join me in making a covenant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.61,0:22:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with the one true God, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.65,0:22:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to carry out all the words of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.04,0:22:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, our God in the heavens . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.54,0:22:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.84,0:22:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.40,0:23:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring them down to the Kidron Valley, and burn them there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.78,0:23:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And desecrate Topheth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so that no one can make their son
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.62,0:23:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or their daughter pass through the fire there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.16,0:23:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is only the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.46,0:23:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help, we will rid the entire land of high places,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.17,0:23:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,every vestige of false worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.05,0:23:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and of everyone who promotes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.06,0:23:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we cleanse the land of Judah, we’ll head north again
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.86,0:23:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to the cities of Samaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.99,0:23:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.67,0:25:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To whom do these graves belong?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.97,0:25:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They belong to the Baal prophets, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.51,0:25:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Take their bones and burn them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.56,0:25:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,on the altar of King Jeroboam.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.81,0:25:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterward, tear it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.29,0:26:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the grave over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.29,0:26:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the grave of the man of the true God
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.33,0:26:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,who foretold these things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.42,0:26:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have done against the altar of Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.35,0:26:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.06,0:26:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not let anyone disturb his bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.73,0:26:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal, save us! Baal, save us!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.27,0:26:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal! Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.57,0:26:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal! Baal! Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.91,0:26:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal! Baal! Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.91,0:26:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal! Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.75,0:26:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.10,0:27:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord the king
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.48,0:27:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is a pale imitation of his grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.35,0:27:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And now he’s turned my own son against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.65,0:27:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.94,0:27:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about standing up for what is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.41,0:27:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal is powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.41,0:27:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can’t you see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.12,0:27:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Powerless?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.21,0:27:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I had sacrificed you in Topheth!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.27,0:27:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No one will ever be able to do that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.98,0:27:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah made sure of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.57,0:28:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.70,0:28:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,everything has finally been accomplished according to the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.37,0:28:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one thing left for us to make right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.75,0:28:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Command the people to hold a Passover to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.92,0:28:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as is written in the book of the covenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.05,0:29:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the people can’t afford the Passover sacrifices?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.43,0:29:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I will contribute cattle to the people, and my own flocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.35,0:29:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With great pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.43,0:29:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Passover has not been held in grand style
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.85,0:29:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,since the days of the Judges.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.63,0:30:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be careful to obey all these words that I am commanding you,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.68,0:30:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that it may always go well with you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.09,0:30:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and your sons after you,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.02,0:30:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“because you are doing what is good and right
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.57,0:31:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the eyes of Jehovah your God.”
